# Deployment Script Restructure - Walkthrough

## What Changed

Replaced `deploy-posh.ps1` (cherry-pick deployment with downtime) with `deploy-v2.ps1` (blue-green zero-downtime deployment).

### Root causes fixed

| Problem | Old Script (v1) | New Script (v2) |
|---------|----------------|-----------------|
| **Missing files** | Cherry-picked specific folders, missed `prisma.config.ts`, `nodemon.json` etc. | Uses a **complete production manifest** at top of script. Add new files there. |
| **25+ sec downtime** | Stopped service *before* `npm ci` + `prisma generate` | Installs deps in parallel dir while old version **stays live** |
| **File lock errors** | `Move-Item` failed because Node held locks | Uses `Rename-Item` (atomic NTFS rename, no locks) |
| **No rollback** | Failed deployments left broken state | **Automatic rollback** if health check fails after cutover |

---

## Files Created/Modified

### [NEW] [deploy-v2.ps1](file:///c:/Apps/Leave%20Tracker/deploy-v2.ps1)

The complete zero-downtime deployment script (1013 lines). Key sections:

#### 10-Step Flow

| Step | What it does | Impact |
|------|-------------|--------|
| 1/10 | **Deployment Guards** | Confirms user tested locally, asks before production push |
| 2/10 | **Pre-Flight Validation** | Verifies ALL required files exist locally before building |
| 3/10 | **Authentication** | SSH credentials for VM1 + VM2 (env vars or interactive) |
| 4/10 | **Build Artifacts** | Vite frontend build + TypeScript backend build |
| 5/10 | **Stage & Package** | Copies all manifest items, verifies, creates zip archives |
| 6/10 | **Connect to VMs** | SSH sessions to Frontend (VM1) + Backend (VM2) |
| 7/10 | **Deploy Frontend** | Atomic swap: dist-next -> dist + Nginx reload (zero downtime) |
| 8/10 | **Deploy Backend** | Blue-green: install in -next, pre-flight on port 5001, atomic cutover (<3s) |
| 9/10 | **Final Health Checks** | Backend API, Frontend root, API proxy through Nginx |
| 10/10 | **Cleanup** | Remove old backups and staging files |

#### Production File Manifest (line ~114)

```powershell
$BackendProductionFiles = @(
    @{ Name = "dist";              IsDir = $true;  SourceDir = "server" },
    @{ Name = "prisma";            IsDir = $true;  SourceDir = "server" },
    @{ Name = "public";            IsDir = $true;  SourceDir = "root"   },
    @{ Name = "package.json";      IsDir = $false; SourceDir = "server" },
    @{ Name = "package-lock.json"; IsDir = $false; SourceDir = "server" },
    @{ Name = "prisma.config.ts";  IsDir = $false; SourceDir = "server" }
)
```

> [!TIP]
> When you add a new file/directory the backend needs, just add it to this manifest. The script will automatically include it in staging, verify it, and deploy it.

---

## Bugs Fixed During Development

1. **Unicode parsing errors** - PowerShell couldn't parse em-dashes and box-drawing characters. Replaced with ASCII.
2. **`$TestPort:` drive reference** - `$TestPort:` was parsed as a variable drive. Fixed with `${TestPort}`.
3. **`ForEach-Object` in here-string** - `$_.Name` inside a here-string broke parsing. Changed to `foreach` loop.
4. **`Select-Object -ExpandProperty` on hashtable** - Hashtables don't support this. Changed to `ForEach-Object { $_.Name }`.
5. **`public/` source directory** - Located at project root, not `server/`. Added `SourceDir` property to manifest.

---

## How to Deploy

```powershell
# Safe test (builds locally, skips all remote operations)
.\deploy-v2.ps1 -DryRun

# Full production deployment
.\deploy-v2.ps1

# With database migration
.\deploy-v2.ps1 -MigrateDb

# CI/CD mode (no prompts)
.\deploy-v2.ps1 -SkipConfirm
```

